	<text xml:lang="la">
		<body>
			<div xml:id="div1" corresp="regest1">
				<p>
					<s n="1" xml:lang="la" type="auto">S. D.</s>
					<s n="2" xml:lang="la" type="auto">Quamquam postremis tuis<note xml:id="fn1" type="footnote" n="1">Brief <ref target="file12940">Nr. 2891</ref> vom 30. April.</note> ad me testatus sis, frater in domino venerande, te non scripturum amplius, nisi cum habueris certissima,<note xml:id="fn2" type="footnote" n="2">Bezug auf <ref target="file12940">Nr. 2891</ref>,<ptr target="qvzl17158-4" type="qv"/>.</note> neque quicquam dubitem de tua fide et diligentia, tamen dictu mirum est, quam impatienter feram tuum silentium, praesertim in tanta varietate rumorum.</s>
				</p>
			</div>
			<div xml:id="div2" corresp="regest2">
				<p>
					<s n="3" xml:lang="la" type="auto">Nunc pro certo dicitur elector<note xml:id="fn3" type="footnote" n="3">Kurfürst <persName>Johann Friedrich I. von Sachsen</persName>. - Siehe dazu den Bericht von <persName>Johannes Haller</persName> in <ref target="file12943">Nr. 2894</ref>,<ptr target="qvzl17159-8" type="qv"/>.</note> captus, modo liberatus iterum, iam dicitur victus et <placeName>Wittenberga</placeName><note xml:id="fn4" type="footnote" n="4"><placeName>Wittenberg</placeName> wurde nach kurzer Belagerung durch den Kaiser am 23. Mai kampflos übergeben; s. <bibl>Scheible, <placeName>Wittenberg</placeName></bibl> 259. - Siehe auch <ref target="file12943">Nr. 2894</ref>,<ptr target="qvzl17159-16" type="qv"/>.</note> deleta funditus, modo praedicatur victor et trium-<pb type="edition" next="204"/>phare <placeName>Wittenbergam</placeName>, caesarem<note xml:id="fn5" type="footnote" n="5"><persName>Karl V.</persName> - Vgl. <ref target="file12955">Nr. 2906</ref>,[3].</note> amisisse bombardas et novas sibi conquirere, dispersum illius exercitum, ipsum tamen instaurare novum.</s>
				</p>
			</div>
			<div xml:id="div3" corresp="regest3">
				<p>
					<s n="4" xml:lang="la" type="auto">Illa tanta dicuntur ex aequo constantia, ut, cui tuto credas, nescias!</s>
					<s n="5" xml:lang="la" type="auto">Nos hic certi habemus nihil.</s>
					<s n="6" xml:lang="la" type="auto">Metuo tamen electoris res peius habere, quam utile sit.</s>
					<s n="7" xml:lang="la" type="auto">Sed erunt et sunt utilia sanctis, quae operatur dominus.<note xml:id="fn6" type="footnote" n="6">Vgl. Röm 8, 28.</note></s>
					<s n="8" xml:lang="la" type="auto">Hunc precemur, ut nos servet.</s>
					<s n="9" xml:lang="la" type="auto">Obsecro, si quid coniecturarum aut certi habes, scribas et <persName>Froschoverum</persName><note xml:id="fn7" type="footnote" n="7"><persName>Christoph Froschauer d.Ä.</persName></note> habeas commendatum.</s>
				</p>
			</div>
			<div xml:id="div4" corresp="regest4">
				<p>
					<s n="10" xml:lang="la" type="auto">Vale cum tuis omnibus.</s>
					<s n="11" xml:lang="la" type="auto">Tiguri, 23. maii 1547.</s>
					<s n="12" xml:lang="la" type="auto">Bullingerus tuus.</s>
				</p>
				<p>
					<note type="address">[Adresse auf der Rückseite:]</note>
					<s n="13" xml:lang="la" type="auto">D. <persName>Ambrosio Blaurero</persName> suo.</s>
					<s n="14" xml:lang="la" type="auto"><placeName>Constantiae</placeName>.<note xml:id="fn8" type="footnote" n="8">Der Überbringer des vorliegenden Briefes war <persName>Christoph Froschauer</persName>; s. oben Z. <ptr target="qvzl17172-1" type="qv"/>.</note></s>
				</p>
			</div>
